trend_summary: Minor infill and street densification occur mainly north-central, yet vegetation remains dominant. A south-west quarry is reclaimed, while riverbank levees and wetlands are upgraded. Water reservoirs are refurbished, and a large circular clearing emerges north-east. Overall form stays moderately compact within extensive tree cover.
notable_changes: Progressive infill housing and tighter street grid in the north-central sector.
Brown south-west extraction site becomes vegetated, indicating reclamation or park creation.
New large circular clearing/structure appears in the north-east after mid-series.
Riverfront levee realignment and wetland expansion along the southern shore.
Water-treatment reservoirs refurbished, with liner colour changes and added basins.
